  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "By default, the scheduler spreads pods by zone, in order to provide some level of reliability for services.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/scheduler/algorithm/priorities/selector_spreading.go#L108\r\n\r\n**What would you like to be added**:\r\n\r\nCluster operators should be able to change this to a topology label that better fits their need.\r\n\r\nThis can be done with a flag to the binary that is set to `zone` by default, so that current behavior remains.\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\n\r\nOn-prem clusters have different topologies than cloud providers. If the scheduler uses the zone topology for default spreading, on-prem cluster operators don't have another alternative but to abuse the zone label even though that might violate its semantic meaning.\r\n\r\n/sig scheduling",
